. Rydel, and Amy N. Vines.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEnglish literatureyMiddle English, 1100-1500xHistory and criticism. 0aPastourellesxHistory and criticism. 0aRape culture in literature. 0aRape in literature. 0aScottish literatureyTo 1700xHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh  a#MeToo Movement.  aConsent in theMiddle Ages.  aEnglish and Scottish pastourelles.  aFemale Subjectivity.  aLyric.  aMargery Kempe.  aSexual Violence.  aStudy of medieval rape culture.  aSurvivor speech.  aWilliam Dunbar.  ahagiography.1 aAllen-Goss, Lucy M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaechle, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaechle, Sarah, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aEdwards, Suzanne M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFlannery, Mary C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarris, Carissa M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarris, Carissa M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJager, Katharine W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiller, Scott David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRobertson, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRydel, Courtney E, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStrakhov, Elizaveta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStrakhov, Elizaveta, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aVines, Amy N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of e